EMAIL, POWERSCHOOL, and TEACHER CONTACT INFO
Refresher for our 6th through 12th grade students that may not remember how to log on to PowerSchool or their email. The link to PowerSchool is easy to find at GwinnSchools.org.
or at https://gwinn.powerschool.com/public/
Login is your student's lunch code
Password is the first 6 numbers of their birthday.
For example 11/22/2004 would be 112220, 1/7/2005 would be 172005.
Email (Mine would have been Brad Pfluger, class of 1994)
94bpflug@gacsk12.org
first 2 digits are the graduation year. (seniors are 20, 6th grade is 26), followed by first initial of first name followed by up to 5 letters of last name. All students have @gacsk12.org.
This email will grant students access into Google Classroom. Teachers are in the process of updating Classrooms daily.
Staff contact information: (Also at GwinnSchools.org)
https://ghs.gwinnschools.org/staff
Please continue to send questions. The best way to get through this challenging time is by being patient, asking questions, and working together.
-Mr. Pfluger MS/HS Principal

post_text: If you would like your sports minded child to participate in a FREE baseline ImPACT concussion test please contact our on-site Gwinn Teen Clinic at 906-372-4002 or email LSpade@mqtco.org. The ImPACT baseline test helps determine the athlete's level of functioning before a concussion. If the athlete sustains a head injury during the sports season, their office can then go back to the baseline test and compare it to the athlete's function level at the time of injury. GO MODELTOWNERS!

Please take a moment and complete the Gwinn Area Community Schools Return to Learn Selection Form. It only takes a couple of minutes, and can be found at the district website, gwinnschools.org. If your internet is limited or poor, or if you experience any difficulties, you may share the information to schools by calling your child's building directly. The questions being asked:
Parent First Name
Parent Last Name
Student First Name
Student Last Name
School Building
Grade
Choice: In Person, Online, or Undecided.

Our plans for in person instruction can be found on our website as well. We are actively developing our online learning plan. We hope to have a detailed plan in the next handful of days to share on the specifics of hour our online instruction will be provided for our families choosing this option.
Please share this information, especially with anyone you may know that is not active on social media or without internet.
Thank you for your patience, support, and efforts to help us communicate with our families and community.

4:45 update for Gwinn High School's Class of 2020 Graduation.
The severe weather is going to arrive soon, and is projected to be pretty clear once it is done. The estimates are now projecting the storm to be wrapping up shortly after 7pm. post_text:
Gwinn High School Graduation 2020 update:
The weather report has improved slightly over the past day or two. We are still on schedule for our outdoor graduation ceremony at 7:00 pm on Friday, June 26th. We will be having the ceremony recorded and it will be available for free, through our YouTube channel, within a few days for anyone unable to attend. Remember to bring lawn chairs and/or blankets for the football field. Also, take into account there is a fair amount of rain possible during the afternoon, so plan accordingly. Masks are encouraged and we appreciate your efforts to follow social distancing guidelines to the best of your ability.

We will be in contact with the national weather service throughout the morning. If the weather takes a turn for the worst, the ceremony will be moved inside. Students will be given 4 tickets for guests to attend the gymnasium ceremony. We are also working toward offering a live-stream YouTube video as well as an "over-flow" option in our cafeteria, if we are forced indoors.

Attention Class of 2020 graduating seniors, families, friends, and community members. Graduation for the Class of 2020 is scheduled for 7:00 pm on Friday 6/26/2020 at McCormick Field. Our graduates will be seated in the bleachers and the audience will be seated in the field area. Please bring your own blankets and chairs and join us for the celebration. At this time, the weather forecast is for about 80 degrees with a chance of evening rain. In the case of inclement weather, we will host the ceremony at 3:00 pm on Saturday 6/27. Face masks are encouraged and social distancing guidelines should be followed at all times.
Graduates should also be checking their school email and Google Classroom for additional information. A School Messenger update will also be going out to the families of graduates.

post_text: Update for current 8th grade students.
shared_text:
Gwinn Middle School PTO
May 30 at 3:22 PM Â·

Hello 8th Grade Students and Parents

Just a quick update on the 8th Grade Great America trip that was cancelled due to the COVID-19 situation.

We would like to give the 8th students who committed to the May 2020 Great America trip one of the following two options:

1. A refund of parent paid money (this excludes ANY and ALL fundraising and concession earnings/volunteering) - if forfeited, this money will be used for upcoming PTO paid events on behalf of Gwinn Middle School students or can be transferred to an upcoming MS sibling

or

2. Attend Great America in May 2021 (current 8th grade students and upcoming 8th grade students will go together) - you will not be charged any additional fees for the trip.

We will be sending letters out at the start of the school year to all parents/students that have committed to the May 2020 trip and allow you ample time to make your decision and return the form to us with your choice. Once you make your decision, it will be final.

Thank you!

Gwinn Middle School PTO

post_text:
A message from Barbie Ward-Thomas, our Food Service Coordinator at GACS:
Hello Friends and Families surrounding Gwinn Michigan.
We are still serving meals for all kids, 18 years or younger, Monday (for Mon & Tues), Wednesday (for Wed & Thursdsay), Friday (for Friday, Sat, and Sunday!)
Serving starts at 11:00 and runs until 12:00 at KIS & GHS.
As for right now we will be running at least until the end of the first week of June...That is June 5th. We may be serving longer based on the govt. support.
Please Please Please share this info with all of your friends and families...IF WE DON'T USE THIS PROGRAM WE WILL LOSE THIS PROGRAM!
The numbers are all pretty inconsistent at GHS. We want to help but we need your support to make this happen. Please understand even if you "don't" believe you "need" this it will still be availabe, so let us help you and then you can help the program! WIN-WIN!!!!
If you have any questions, concerns or considerations, please email me at bward@gwinn.k12.mi.us
See you soon, I hope!

EMAIL, POWERSCHOOL, and TEACHER CONTACT INFO

Refresher for and 6th through 12th grade students that may not remember how to log on to PowerSchool or their email. The link to PowerSchool is easy to find at GwinnSchools.org.
or at https://gwinn.powerschool.com/public/
Login is your student's lunch code
Password is the first 6 numbers of their birthday.
For example 11/22/2004 would be 112220, 1/7/2005 would be 172005.

Email (Mine would have been Brad Pfluger, class of 1994)
94bpflug@gacsk12.org
first 2 digits are the graduation year. (seniors are 20, 6th grade is 26), followed by first initial of first name followed by up to 5 letters of last name. All students have @gacsk12.org.

This email will grant students access into Google Classroom. A few teachers are in the process of creating a Classroom and updating information.

Staff contact information: (Also at GwinnSchools.org)
https://ghs.gwinnschools.org/staff

Please continue to send questions. The best way to get through this confusing time is by being patient, asking questions, and working together.
-Mr. Pfluger MS/HS Principal

post_text:
Just a quick update for those of you looking for information about the upcoming move from in-school to distance learning for Gwinn MS/HS.
This transition has many challenging aspects to it and we are attempting to do what is best for our students. We have been discussing many topics ranging from what the instruction will look like, what is expected of students, and what technology our students and teachers will need to make this possible.
What is needed at this time is patience. Our intention is to work on our plan as defined by the Michigan Department of Education and have it approved.
We will share details of this plan, and other critical information as it becomes available.
Thank you for your patience and support through these challenging times.
Reminder for students to be checking their email and Google Classrooms frequently. Juniors that took internship applications need to reach out to Mrs. Viitala. We need to get the information to make sure we get you signed up and hopefully placed for next year.

post_text:
Students in Mrs. Humphrey's 7th grade science class have been studying how to identify where volcanoes will form on Earth and understand their behavior.

To understand the relationship between eruption frequency and volcanic explosivity, students played Jenga. Students keep track of the number of blocks pulled from the stack each game (mimicking the passing of time) and then measure the distance the farthest block flew from the "volcano" upon eruption when the stack falls (mimicking volcanic explosivity).

Through this activity, students discover that the largest volcanic eruptions will have the lowest frequency.
#GwinnSchools #ModeltownerPride

Gwinn High School Senior Student of the Month for February of 2020 is sponsored by M.J. VanDamme, Inc, Townerâs Pastries, Hairlines, Up North Lodge, Gwinn Inn/Pizza Machine, and the GEA.
Congratulations to Ms. Zaida Pearson, the Valedictorian of the GHS Class of 2020. While at GHS, Zaida has taken all or our advances/honors courses as well as participating in an internship at Kids-R-Us Child Development Center, Inc. this year. She also mentors students through Big Brothers Big Sisters. Zaida is also a member of our Peer to Peer tutoring program, where she assists struggling students in becoming better students. Zaida excels at communication, making connections, and organization. Outside of school, Zaidaâs favorite thing to do is coach gymnastics. She coaches 4 to 7 year olds at PEAK Gymnastics and has taken on the role as Pre-team Director. She has also volunteered her time to host a free summer gymnastics program for area youth. Zaida plans on attending University of Michigan in the fall to pursue a degree in psychology.
#ModeltownerPride #GwinnSchools

LUNCH SERVER NEEDED

Gwinn Area Community Schools is seeking candidates for one (1) part-time lunch server at Gwinn Middle/High School.

Position is two hours/day (11:30 am until 1:30 pm, Monday-Friday) with a starting pay of $11.35/hour.

Applicants must meet all school board requirements and pass a criminal background check. Serve Safe certification is required along with the ability to lift 30-50 pounds.

Interested candidates should apply by submitting a letter of interest and completed application (available at www.gwinn.k12.mi.us) to: Barbie Ward-Thomas, Food Service Director, PO Box 447, Gwinn, MI 49841. Applications are due Friday, February 28, 2020 or until position is filled.

post_text: Thank you to one of our long time "rivals" for your continued support and kindness during this challenging time. What a great example of the supporting mentality our great 906 family has.
shared_text:
Negaunee High School Booster Club
February 4 at 9:01 PM Â·

As many of you know, Gwinn Area Community Schools unexpectedly lost their head football coach and a pillar in their community last month. Touching many lives not only on the field, but off it as well. A mentor to all he coached and someone who made a difference in the community at large.

To honor his legacy and the family he leaves behind, we will be donating our portion of the 50/50 drawing from our boys basketball game against Gwinn this Friday to the Dion Brown family account at Honor Credit Union.

Typically, our 50/50 is how we fund our Booster Club scholarships, however, sometimes there are special circumstances such as this. His passion for athletics, community, the kids he coached and making a difference in the lives of those that knew him will be remembered by all.

Students in Mrs. Micheau and Mr. Sinnaeve's health class learned how to use an Epinephrine autoInjector with EpiPen trainers today. They are very easy to use, and with a little practice and education, it can help give someone the confidence to use it correctly in an emergency situation. The students learned when an EpiPen should be administered based off of severe or mild symptoms. The students also watched a few real life stories showing food allergies that have caused anaphylaxis.
Thank you Mrs. Micheau and Mr. Sinnaeve for teaching our students such a life saving skill.
#ModeltownerPride #GwinnSchools

Also, our Student Council is going to use this week starting on Monday, January 27th as Snow Fest Week which replaces our typical winter homecoming. There will also be a dance but we are waiting to hear if the Junior Class will be offering that on Friday night or a different date. Certain things like hall decorating and crowning a king and queen along with assembly games will not take place. Stay tuned and please help to spread the word about the new date for our high school boys basketball game versus Bark River-Harris. GO MODELTOWNERS!

Congratulations to the 6th-8th Grade Gwinn Middle School Students of the Month for November, sponsored by The Middle School PTO and the Gwinn Education Association (Teachers).
6th Grade: Ms. Harlow Eberle. Harlow is a member of our GMS Take-a-Hike Club and Marvel Movie club. She is described as humble, kind, and hard working.
7th Grade: Ms. Leela Monarch. Leela is a gifted student and is excelling in her academics. She is said to be a great problem solver with a lot of "spunk."
8th Grade: Ms. Jessica Jerome. Jessica enjoys being around animals, drawing, reading, and playing the flute. Jessica is a member of the GMS Take-a-Hike club and teachers tell us she is an outstanding leader.
#GwinnSchools #ModeltownerPride

Gwinn High School Senior Student of the Month for November was sponsored by Gwinn Floral & Gifts, Stepping Stones Daycare & Pre-School, Gwinn Inn/Pizza Machine, Up North Lodge, and the Gwinn Education Association.
Congratulations to senior Kadie LaRock. Kadie is an active member of our Drama productions, tennis team, Student Council, National Honor Society, Peer 2 Peer program, and Yearbook staff here at GHS. She has aspirations to get a degree in Elementary Education with a minor in Theater.
#ModeltownerPride #GwinnSchools

Congratulations to the 9th-11th Grade Gwinn High School Students of the Month for November, sponsored by The Pizza Machine in Gwinn and the Gwinn Education Association (Teachers).
9th Grade: Ms. Emily Bandle. Emily is an expert on our drama soundboard and is described by teachers as an outgoing, creative, and focused student that is a true leader in the classroom.
10th Grade: Ms. Brittany Ouellette. Brittany is outstanding writer, avid reader, and excels in both mathematics and science. She is looking to enter the medical field after high school.
11th Grade: Mr. Chris Packard. Chris is a standout performer in Drama, Band, and Quiz Bowl. Teachers describe him as kind, thoughtful, and curious.
#GwinnSchools #ModeltownerPride
